Chipotle Pumpkin Soup

2 tbsp olive oil
1 chopped medium yellow onion
3 chopped garlic cloves
1 tsp ground cumin
1-2 chopped chipotle peppers (canned in adobo, 1 for mild, 2 for spicy)
8 c chopped, cooked pumpkin (3x15oz cans of puree pumpkin)*
4-6 c chicken stock
1 tsp dried oregano
2 tsp salt
2 tbsp lime juice

Heat oil in large pot (8 quart) on medium high heat. Add the oinions and cook for 3-4 min, until softened. Add the garlic, cumin, and chipotle; cook for 1 min more. Add the pumpkin, chicken stock, oregano, and salt. Bring to a simmer, reduce the heat and simmer for 20 min, partially covered. Remove the soup from heat. Working in batches of 2 c each, puree the soup, holding down the lid of your blender tightly while pureeing. Return the pureed soup to the pot. Add lime juice. Adjust seasonings to taste, adding more salt, cumin, oregano, or chipotle to taste. Serve with toasted pumpkin seeds (pepitas) crema fresca, and cilantro.
